description: The point shapefile shows locations of quakes with magnitude of 2.5 or more and worldwide quakes of magnitude of 4.5 or more. This includes the latest quake in China, at magnitude 6.9, it struck at a shallow depth of 10 KM (nearly 6.6 miles). Subsequent quakes of magnitude 5 or more also were at the same depth and one was at a shallow depth of 4 KM (2.5 Miles). Look elsewhere on Finder! for the quake related information using keyword search of "quake", "china quake", disaster.
